def grubbs_test(x, alpha=0.05):
   n = len(x)
   mean_x = np.mean(x)
   sd_x = np.std(x)
   numerator = max(abs(x-mean_x))
   g_calc = numerator/sd_x
   t_value = stats.t.ppf(1 - alpha / (2 * n), n - 2) #   Precent Point Function
   g_crit = ((n - 1) * np.sqrt(np.square(t_value))) / (np.sqrt(n) * np.sqrt(n - 2 + np.square(t_value)))
   return g_calc > g_crit

def DixonQ_test(x):
    q_table = 0.337 #  Q     95%  21 
    x_s = sorted(x)
    q_calc = abs(x_s[-2] - x_s[-1])/abs(x_s[0] - x_s[-1])

    return q_calc > q_table
